args:
When the party departs the Halidom, they are
greeted by Chelle on her landship before setting
off for North Grastaea. Even as the prince's
heart is filled with expectation and unease,
he swears to grow a great deal in the unfamiliar
lands that await him.
After parting with Leonidas and Chelle,\nwe all began preparations for the journey.
The hectic days melted away as we did\nour best to ensure things would proceed\nsmoothly in our absence.
Finally, we set out from the Halidom,\nseen off by the soldiers who would\ndefend the castle in our absence.
I've got a tiny suitcase for clothes and a\nhuge suitcase for cake! ...That's how\nyou're supposed to do it, right?

I've taught those remaining the proper
ways to clean, do laundry, and handle
kitchen work, so matters of the household
should all be in order.
All I need is this axe and some grub,\nbut when's that sister'a yers plannin'\nto show up? She's late as hell!
And why did she insist we meet up\nin such a remote place as this?
Say, doesn't something about all of this\nfeel familiar? Like we've done it before?
Now that you mention it, yes.
I don't really follow, I'm afraid.
A massive structure is approaching\nfrom ahead. Exercise caution.\n▷Something's coming our way!◁
And I remember that darn shadow!\nWe're all gonna be squashed!
Hurry up, Brother! If you stand there with\nyour jaw agape any longer, you will draw\nflies and I shall be forced to leave you!
Eee hee hee! How does it feel to have\nanother ride atop the Gran Fiore?
Shocking, actually. I was thinking we were\ngoing to hoof it all the way to the north.
My dear, you've no right to call yourself a\ngentleman if you would coerce a lady into\ntraveling all that way on FOOT.
With this mobile palace, we can travel to\nNorth Grastaea without exhausting a lick\nof our strength in the process.
And of course, we'll have banquets\nand dances to keep our spirits high!
You're really something, Chelle.\nSeriously, I would have just walked.
Eee hee hee! Oh, you! Stop!\n...But not really. Continue, please.
Ah! We should pass Valkaheim soon.
We've already come that far? Wow.\nI suppose Leonidas is busy at work\nin the castle as we speak.
(Thank you, my brother. I swear not to let\nthe time you've given me go to waste.)

Increase deployment on highways and in
urban areas, and examine the times and
routes of patrols. I want order restored
to this country with all speed.

Also, take steps to build a surveillance
network for watching the Ilian Church.
If a fly sneezes in this land, I want to
be informed how far it traveled.
(Alberia is troubled from within and\nwithout, but I will show no mercy\nto any who would threaten it.)
(Overcome what trials may come,\nmy brother, and seize hold of the truth.)
(For this Nedrick man will stand astride\nyour path as a wall divides a border...)
So the seventh scion is heading\nfor Grams, is he?
This land is a bigger and more diverse\nplace than South Grastaea.

He is but a tiny fish wading from the local
rivers into a vast ocean; I wonder if he
will find his way to the truth without being
swallowed up by swells.
And if he does manage to learn the truth,\nwill he have the magnanimity to accept it?\nI will wait and see, but expect little.
(I pray for a safe journey for you—and that\nwe might be together once more.)
(I'm coming to where you are, Zethia.\nI'm coming to North Grastaea.)
(And once I'm there, maybe I'll learn the\nanswer to the riddle of who I am.)
(I'd be lying if I said I wasn't scared,\nand I'd give anything to have you with\nme during this journey.)
(But I feel that if I can face who I am,\nnew paths will open to me.)
(I'm going to absorb as much as I can\nthroughout this journey and find the\nstrength to accept whoever I am.)
(I'm sure that seeing new towns and\nmeeting new people will broaden my\nhorizons and learnings.)
(I will grow. I will become stronger.\nAnd then...)
His Highness is nowhere to be found.
He was inside a little while ago.
{player_name} located.\n▷He's on the deck of the ship!◁
Hey, boss! Quit with the lollygaggin'\nand get yer butt over here!
Chelle wishes to propose a toast.
It's time to begin this most thrilling\nsend-off party, brother dear.
I'll be back in a second, everyone.
(Together with these irreplaceable friends,\nI'm going to rescue you. So just stay safe\nuntil then.)
